main sequence (MS), the starburst sequence and the quenched galaxy
cloud. We find that the MS slope becomes flatter when higher stellar
mass cuts are adopted, and that the apparent slope change observed at
high masses depends on the SFR estimation method. In addition, the
multi-Gaussian decomposition reveals the presence of a starburst
